<problem id="fs-id1859287">
 <para id="import-auto-id1609369">A <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mtext>-MΩ</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{1 "." "00""-M" %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> voltmeter is placed in parallel with a <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>75</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>-k</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"75" "." 0"-k" %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> resistor in a circuit. (a) Draw a circuit diagram of the connection. (b) What is the resistance of the combination? (c) If the voltage across the combination is kept the same as it was across the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>75</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>-k</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"75" "." 0"-k" %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> resistor alone, what is the percent increase in current? (d) If the current through the combination is kept the same as it was through the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>75</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>-k</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"75" "." 0"-k" %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> resistor alone, what is the percentage decrease in voltage? (e) Are the changes found in parts (c) and (d) significant? Discuss.</para></problem></exercise>

